    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix buffer boundary check in RLC PDU decoder functions\n\n### Summary\nThe RLC PDU decoder functions in the gNB RLC module had missing buffer boundary checks that could cause memory access beyond allocated buffers. When processing RLC PDUs from the F1AP interface between CU and DU, the decoder would increment byte counters without verifying buffer limits, leading to incorrect data size calculations and potential message corruption or loss downstream.\n\nSpecifically, both `rlc_pdu_decoder_align()` and `get_bit()` functions were incrementing `decoder->byte` without checking if the new value would exceed `decoder->size`. This caused the decoder to report incorrect byte positions, which were then used by downstream functions to calculate data segment boundaries.\n\nThe issue manifested as corrupted RLC data transfers and intermittent connection drops during high-throughput scenarios where PDU boundaries aligned with buffer limits.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/rlc_v2/rlc_pdu.c`: Added buffer boundary checks in `rlc_pdu_decoder_align()` and `get_bit()` functions to prevent `decoder->byte` from exceeding `decoder->size`\n- `openair2/LAYER2/rlc_v2/rlc_pdu.h`: No changes required to header definitions\n\n"
}